## Mutation Type Required: {{ mutation_type }}

### Mutation Type Definitions
- empty_input: Leave required fields blank and verify error messages appear
- boundary_values: Use minimum (0, 1), maximum (INT_MAX, 255 chars), and just-over values
- special_characters: Unicode characters, emoji 🔥, SQL-like strings (read-only), quotes, newlines
- invalid_format: Wrong data type — letters in numeric field, invalid email, future-only date in past field
- wrong_credentials: Incorrect password, non-existent user, locked/inactive account
- sql_injection_attempt: Submit SQL-like strings as inputs, verify app handles them safely (not testing actual injection)
- xss_attempt: Submit <script> tag as input, verify it is escaped in output (not testing actual XSS)
- concurrent_submission: Rapid double-click or double-submit, verify no duplicate processing
- session_expiry: Test behaviour after session timeout (mock or stub the timeout)
- max_length_exceeded: Input strings longer than any visible maxlength, very long text

